data.value: The "Architectural Design Decision Support System” or "AD-DSS" is developed to assist stakeholders in building projects to evaluate architectural design alternatives in terms of life-cycle performance. The AD-DSS is developed and designed by Abdullah Ali Al-Saggaf with email: engr.alsaggaf@gmail.com, and mobile: 0542554541, as a part of the thesis: “Developing MCDA System to Evaluate the Life-Cycle Performance of Buildings" submitted for the requirements of the degree of Master of Science in Civil Engineering [Construction Engineering], Faculty of Engineering, King Abdulaziz University, Jeddah, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia (Ramadan 1440H – May 2019G).
